article.description: — Tai'Reon Joseph had 21 points in Southern's 80-66 win over UAPB on Saturday night.
article.headline: Southern defeats UAPB 80-66
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. -- — Tai'Reon Joseph had 21 points in Southern's 80-66 win over UAPB on Saturday night. Joseph shot 9 for 18 (1 for 5 from 3-point range) and 2 of 3 from the free-throw line for the Jaguars (10-9, 4-2 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Derrick Tezeno scored 17 points and added five rebounds. Jariyon Wilkens shot 5 of 8 from the field and 3 for 4 from the line to finish with 13 points. The Golden Lions (8-11, 3-3) were led by Kylen Milton, who posted 20 points and seven rebounds. Rashad Williams added 15 points for UAPB. Lonnell Martin Jr. also had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
